This paper deals with learning controllers for robotic tasks, specifically bipedal locomotion, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Bayesian optimization (BO) for tuning controllers is a machine learning approach, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of simulation to improve sample efficiency, which involves system identification and control theory, falling under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses computer vision techniques to analyze the performance of the controllers, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
